  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2697",
  "title": "RFC: connectConfigure",
  "body": "* Start Date: 2018-02-05\r\n\r\n# Summary\r\n\r\nA connector for third-party integrations which doesn't have any rendering to set options for the InstantSearch instance. These options are sent on every `search` or `searchForFacetValues`.\r\n\r\n# Motivation\r\n\r\nHaving `searchParameters` in `instantsearch()` makes sense for a static configuration, but as soon as you want to make it dynamic, it makes more sense as a widget, than as a parameter for InstantSearch. The main reason being that a widget is easier to change than a parameter on InstantSearch, and will be more consistent\r\n\r\n# Detailed design\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst widgetFactory = connectConfigure(\r\n (state, isFirstRendering) => {\r\n   // render nothing\r\n },\r\n () => {\r\n   // just a necessary noop\r\n }\r\n);\r\n\r\nconst widget = widgetFactory({\r\n analytics: true,\r\n ruleContexts: [\"fancy context\", \"add dogs\"]\r\n});\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(widget);\r\n\r\n// later, if you want to change something:\r\nconst newWidget = widgetFactory({\r\n analytics: true,\r\n ruleContexts: [\"boring context\", \"add dogs\"]\r\n});\r\nsearch.addWidget(newWidget);\r\nsearch.removeWidget(widget);\r\n```\r\n\r\n# How We Teach This\r\n\r\nAdd new entry in docs, implement in Vue InstantSearch and Angular InstantSearch as a widget.\r\n\r\n# Drawbacks\r\n\r\nThis connector doesn't need a widget which renders anything, although in some cases it _could_ make sense as a widget which is reconstructed if the parameters change, as a fallback just on top of a real custom widget. We should not take that usecase too much in account, but rather encourage custom widgets for that use case\r\n\r\n# Alternatives\r\n\r\nUse the helper directly in the libraries, but this is complicated as that would make components inconsistent\r\n\r\n# Unresolved questions\r\n\r\n- What happens on unmount\r\n- What happens on conflicting parameters",
